08492nam a22010815i 9781641890540DE-B159720220302035458.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220302t20202020xxk    fo  d z      eng d  a97816418905407 a10.1515/97816418905402doi  a(DE-B1597)548856  a(OCoLC)1156664464  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxkcGB-LDS 7aANT0050002bisacsh04a025.842231 aCampagnolo, Alberto, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aBook Conservation and Digitization :bThe Challenges of Dialogue and Collaboration /cAlberto Campagnolo. 1aLeeds : bARC Humanities Press, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (316 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aCollection Development, Cultural Heritage, and Digital Humanities00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tList of Illustrations -- tIntroduction -- tPART ONE: BOOKS AS OBJECTS AND THEIR DIGITIZATION -- tChapter 1. Understanding the Artifactual Value of Books -- tChapter 2. Conservation and Digitization: A Difficult Balance? -- tPART TWO: CONSERVATION AND DIGITIZATION IN PRACTICE -- tIntroduction -- tChapter 3. Conservation towards Large- Scale Digitization at the Vatican Library -- tChapter 4. Large- Scale Digitization at The National Archives -- tChapter 5. British Library/ Qatar Foundation Partnership and the Digitization Project: A Case Study about Conservation Processes within Mass Digitization of Library Material -- tChapter 6. The Digitization of Medieval Western Manuscripts at Wellcome Collection -- tChapter 7. Caring for the Object during Digitization of Written Heritage: The Strategy of the Herzog August Library Wolfenbüttel -- tChapter 8. The Great Parchment Book Project -- tChapter 9. The Development of the Language of Bindings Thesaurus -- tChapter 10. Spectral Imaging to Aid Preservation and Conservation of Cultural Heritage -- tChapter 11. Multispectral Imaging for Special Collection Materials -- tPART THREE: CONSERVATORS AND DIGITIZATION EXPERTS IN DIALOGUE -- tIntroduction -- tChapter 12. The Digitization of Manuscripts from the Point of View of a Book Conservator -- tChapter 13. Implementing Advanced Digital Imaging Research in Cultural Heritage: Building Relationships between Conservators and Computational Imaging Scientists -- tChapter 14. Coda: Concluding Thoughts on Digital Surrogates -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe successful transmediation of books and documents through digitization requires the synergetic partnership of many professional figures, that have what may sometimes appear as contrasting goals at heart. On one side, there are those who look after the physical objects and strive to preserve them for future generations, and on the other those involved in the digitization of the objects, the information that they contain, and the management of the digital data. These complementary activities are generally considered as separate and when the current literature addresses both fields, it does so strictly within technical reports and guidelines, concentrating on procedures and optimal workflow, standards, and technical metadata. In particular, more often than not, conservation is presented as ancillary to digitization, with the role of the conservator restricted to the preparation of items for scanning, with no input into the digital product, leading to misunderstanding and clashes of interests. Surveying a variety of projects and approaches to the challenging conservation-digitization balance and fostering a dialogue amongst practitioners, this book aims at demonstrating that a dialogue between apparently contrasting fields not only is possible, but it is in fact desirable and fruitful. Only through the synergetic collaboration of all people involved in the digitization process, conservators included, can cultural digital objects that represent more fully the original objects and their materiality be generated, encouraging and enabling new research and widening the horizons of scholarship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aBooksxConservation and restoration. 0aBooks. 0aDigital humanities. 0aDigital preservation. 0aLibrary materialsxDigitization. 4aHistory. 7aANTIQUES & COLLECTIBLES / Books.2bisacsh  abook conservation.  acultural heritage.  adigital humanities.  adigitization.  amultispectral imaging.1 aCampagnolo, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorbach, Almuth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Stefani, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrance, Fenella G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarzo, Flavio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNúñez Gaitán, Ángela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPickwoad, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuandt, Abigail B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSignorello, Stefania, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Philippa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTerras, Melissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThompson-Baum, Catt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aToth, Michael B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVelios, Athanasios, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruytert